info.headline: High Wind Warning issued October 29 at 4:29AM PDT until October 30 at 10:00PM PDT by NWS SanDiego
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PDT MONDAY... * WHAT...Northeast winds 20 to 40 mph with gusts to 60 mph. Isolated gusts to 75 mph in wind-prone passes and canyons. * WHERE...Santa Ana Mountains and Foothills and Orange County Inland Areas. * WHEN...From 11 PM Saturday to 10 PM PDT Monday. * IMPACTS...Strong winds could damage trees and other objects. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds will peak this morning into this afternoon.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
